-- Clinton Voices Concern for Hungary Democracy in Letter, Nol Says
-- B y   Z o l t a n   S i m o n
-- 2011-12-27T11:54:22Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-12-27/clinton-voices-concern-for-hungary-democracy-in-letter-nol-says.html
U.S. Secretary of State  Hillary Clinton  expressed her concerns about the state of  Hungary ’s
democracy in a letter to Premier  Viktor Orban , Nepszabadsag
reported on its website, citing unidentified officials in
 Washington .  Clinton wrote about her concerns for the erosion of checks
and balances, for the overhaul of the judiciary and for the
freedom of religion and the press, according to the  website .
Clinton’s letter was dated Dec. 23, Nol.hu said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
